In England, in the seven days to 05 March, there were 209,082 new confirmed cases (369.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 February, there were 173,708 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 20% (35,374 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 March is 16,425,663 (29,046.2 cases per 100,000 population).
